# <type>(<scope>): <short summary, imperative, ≤ 50 chars>
#
# <body — what & why, wrap at ~72 chars. "How" is in the code.>
#
# <footer — e.g. "Closes #123", "BREAKING CHANGE: ...">
#
# Signed-off-by: Your Name <you@example.com>   ← added automatically by `git commit -s`
#
# ── Conventional Commits ────────────────────────────────────────────
#   type:  feat | fix | docs | refactor | test | build | ci | chore
#   scope: optional, e.g. (costmap), (controller)
#
#   examples:
#     fix(costmap): clamp inflation radius to map resolution
#     feat(controller): add configurable goal tolerance
#     docs: explain rolling→distro backport flow
#
# Remember: sign off every commit  →  git commit -s
# Full guide: CONTRIBUTING.md
